{"title": "Elevator School", "content": "Also called an escalator school. An kind of school consisting of an institution which offers education from elementary or middle school (or even from kindergarten) until the university.\n\nOften, elementary school, middle school, high school, and college are separate institutions requiring that prospective students pass rigid entrance examinations at each transition. Elevator schools, however, allow students to move to the next educational level without having to take the standard entrance exams. (In particular, they allow students to bypass the notoriously hellish high-school entrance examinations.) Despite or perhaps because of this, elevator schools often themselves require students to pass an examination to gain admission at all.\n\nIn most countries, this is simply what the public school system does, taking in any and all students of the appropriate age living in a defined geographic area. Some countries (such as Japan) almost all private schools are elevator schools and they are typically very expensive and prestigious, so expect the student body to display Luxury Tropes.\n\nNote that it's still entirely possible to flunk out of these schools, so they don't work as an explanation for lazy or frequently-absent students. What they do is provide a quick and easy way to realistically have characters of very different ages in the same school setting.\n\nNot to be confused with Wayside School, where nobody uses the elevators anyway.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/ElevatorSchool", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/WaysideSchool", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/RevolutionaryGirlUtena", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/CLAMPSchoolDetectives", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/X1999", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/TsubasaReservoirChronicle", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/XxxHolic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/SailorMoon", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/MahouSenseiNegima", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/OuranHighSchoolHostClub", "